{"type":"message","id":"33f48c83","parentId":"cc585520","timestamp":"2026-04-06T11:37:07.843Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Finding dispatch messages**\n\nI need to continue by locating the dispatch message, which might be in another session that's been deleted. The user only asks me to continue, so that's my focus. I'll check if the session file exists in sessions.json. It seems like the current session doesn't have the dispatch, so I'll parse through sessions.json to see if any metadata or previous session information is available. Hopefully, something will turn up!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0dfadbd9e117bfd10169d39ad2ab1c8197b609dee2c0a29146\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp05rWQVVPKORiONUQs4SlpFLmRzZta3vFL5Q_eJLwdI_4QEdGaji4WRfOwMhSMCdVzyWpkl9HKQNlWQaUebD4vhzLRuxifDRnLFKtzAISdVamjehDNiPI5bxGIc5i90nEuVVovIUYnXXyaeliIfmaRvnja3oqyTTLSZXnsdgN3gb0CpibtoQl98-tYFFmM77QINdQMKskrURumdXEbmsUC5-wfz2VWKfNPEO5YltTvSqyNx_ZdIUnnQctJsIbhxHlFm0mlQF_6ls1KaJysVjNeZRL55BlJmF36S43Id2yt7Jtw6h44fovkZc-twl8xloQdSe-lT3uSh4eLeolwm6dGM9tJf_vWeMCUgdpM4p3d1ap6AS0Hf528TfsuEVTAFOa8IDlLtmmAWz20u904-QdamaQV9sjkm9DOeuZiOyMHQjR7AWMjlrGrLuNPbirkhSaOjkCrTqOp7EyTOwba9DiDCcwlVHDDlkjzgxykTYZt8TDW4nYt8UOFhn54m0avxe6bik-diqHlpUJvFGi8nl0JSV7i2T_zadi_3kdcpAokDtrtOpt588uS8b-OxJsWlToTrrZ4k7yeTdUbW_vxCZk9RbAsSnYOMAR3MeG4N_l7i4F0Gg69Z0C4r1i-NWQ8sQH9YPNWkKzXBubpyzgTKxcRXM7wGUYLvo6EQAfLmEy_1KuGy34FsVr66bIHqxHBhb8HJU_FJD9yQE9PlzPgF2olLPliK8DC9edCLVevnbvtytwN4pcYE8M3xZgKXBLExU7E8Hl_B4F8fm90XfxRAyWmh3m0B-6Lad4D73UQyZlYB8SOaIcrZcfD9DPSSfWmMg1UYAFjRu--Za1vBljRr319b3w3TQ0i39yX6c_vxz2Iac-d7okceGal-7WAw59NTJZ-SZChg-GmLaWsLTDMGSBZZ4rSi_7zXW3KaBjWgWddO-cfmcJjtIPfL_F_UxMX63AMPQOKi1lOsy5oxTNQU-Sn0FaJKVWv5wtJTCDo2ASo5JNSRahjVSO1LrVA2_3kg4Yik313SAqOxjp8pSFz5THofpRn-jVWdg6WO_EfZU4Sx5N0xRL4ItkFz9HfSDanlarVph0oOwi33rSHWXkRSaHsC-Cw2UARoNZ2H9YQLKnTPZeDp6d878MyJfZkSGCAf9l-l9B-aMJKAU1HljGkigvsJxbGvd5hhZtNU4mM30AJiju8iZY2EO8vNK9lv9LTOsnDr3s\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Finding dispatch messages**\\n\\nI need to continue by locating the dispatch message, which might be in another session that's been deleted. The user only asks me to continue, so that's my focus. I'll check if the session file exists in sessions.json. It seems like the current session doesn't have the dispatch, so I'll parse through sessions.json to see if any metadata or previous session information is available. Hopefully, something will turn up!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"Preciso recuperar o dispatch original para saber qual candidate_set avaliar. Vou procurar isso no histórico local da sessão anterior.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0dfadbd9e117bfd10169d39ad6158481978a238d8e17b2ff15\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_RqMpOZJMepvb6I4AUaiPdLQc|fc_0dfadbd9e117bfd10169d39ad7889081979a297036ae90fd86","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"sessions/sessions.json"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"sessions/sessions.json\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_aTirhjJSkDMbmZHXkazWRCXz|fc_0dfadbd9e117bfd10169d39ad788a08197a3dbc42c2953dc4b","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"sessions/459e3484-0729-4eb2-9c7e-04604b5eb8d0.jsonl.deleted.2026-04-06T11-33-58.407Z","offset":1,"limit":250},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"sessions/459e3484-0729-4eb2-9c7e-04604b5eb8d0.jsonl.deleted.2026-04-06T11-33-58.407Z\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":250}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_nkg2eXlT9FJJJFI6z4p5XfvH|fc_0dfadbd9e117bfd10169d39ad788a88197869e57cef024a61f","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"sessions/e6a4c873-ff94-4915-bbcc-d81602c273cf.jsonl.deleted.2026-04-06T11-36-20.546Z","offset":1,"limit":250},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"sessions/e6a4c873-ff94-4915-bbcc-d81602c273cf.jsonl.deleted.2026-04-06T11-36-20.546Z\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":250}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_XkTePis0DqdbIHxRMjdPTOdP|fc_0dfadbd9e117bfd10169d39ad788b081979be9def66c57841b","name":"read","arguments":{"path":".openclaw/workspace-state.json"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\".openclaw/workspace-state.json\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":17875,"output":268,"cacheRead":19328,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37471,"cost":{"input":0.044687500000000005,"output":0.00402,"cacheRead":0.0048319999999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.053539500000000004}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775475408942,"responseId":"resp_0dfadbd9e117bfd10169d39ad197748197b5abd01528b75495"}}
{"type":"message","id":"3faafaaa","parentId":"33f48c83","timestamp":"2026-04-06T11:37:09.429Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_RqMpOZJMepvb6I4AUaiPdLQc|fc_0dfadbd9e117bfd10169d39ad7889081979a297036ae90fd86","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"agent:op_s4_candidate_evaluator:main\": {\n    \"sessionId\": \"e6a4c873-ff94-4915-bbcc-d81602c273cf\",\n    \"updatedAt\": 1775475382173,\n    \"skillsSnapshot\": {\n      \"prompt\": \"\\n\\nThe following skills provide specialized instructions for specific tasks.\\nUse the read tool to load a skill's file when the task matches its description.\\nWhen a skill file references a relative path, resolve it against the skill directory (parent of SKILL.md / dirname of the path) and use that absolute path in tool commands.\\n\\n<available_skills>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>clawflow</name>\\n    <description>Use when work should span one or more detached tasks but still behave like one job with a single owner context. ClawFlow is the runtime substrate under authoring layers like Lobster, acpx, or plain code. Keep conditional logic in the caller; use ClawFlow for flow identity, waiting, outputs, and user-facing emergence.</description>\\n    <location>~/AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\clawflow\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>clawflow-inbox-triage</name>\\n    <description>Example ClawFlow authoring pattern for inbox triage. Use when messages need different treatment based on intent, with some routes notifying immediately, some waiting on outside answers, and others rolling into a later summary.</description>\\n    <location>~/AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\clawflow-inbox-triage\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>coding-agent</name>\\n    <description>Delegate coding tasks to Codex, Claude Code, or Pi agents via background process. Use when: (1) building/creating new features or apps, (2) reviewing PRs (spawn in temp dir), (3) refactoring large codebases, (4) iterative coding that needs file exploration. NOT for: simple one-liner fixes (just edit), reading code (use read tool), thread-bound ACP harness requests in chat (for example spawn/run Codex or Claude Code in a Discord thread; use sessions_spawn with runtime:&quot;acp&quot;), or any work in ~/clawd workspace (never spawn agents here). Claude Code: use --print --permission-mode bypassPermissions (no PTY). Codex/Pi/OpenCode: pty:true required.</description>\\n    <location>~/AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\coding-agent\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>gemini</name>\\n    <description>Gemini CLI for one-shot Q&amp;A, summaries, and generation.</description>\\n    <location>~/AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\gemini\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>gh-issues</name>\\n    <description>Fetch GitHub issues, spawn sub-agents to implement fixes and open PRs, then monitor and address PR review comments. Usage: /gh-issues [owner/repo] [--label bug] [--limit 5] [--milestone v1.0] [--assignee @me] [--fork user/repo] [--watch] [--interval 5] [--reviews-only] [--cron] [--dry-run] [--model glm-5] [--notify-channel -1002381931352]</description>\\n    <location>~/AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\gh-issues\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>github</name>\\n    <description>GitHub operations via `gh` CLI: issues, PRs, CI runs, code review, API queries. Use when: (1) checking PR status or CI, (2) creating/commenting on issues, (3) listing/filtering PRs or issues, (4) viewing run logs. NOT for: complex web UI interactions requiring manual browser flows (use browser tooling when available), bulk operations across many repos (script with gh api), or when gh auth is not configured.</description>\\n    <location>~/AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\github\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>healthcheck</name>\\n    <description>Host security hardening and risk-tolerance configuration for OpenClaw deployments. Use when a user asks for security audits, firewall/SSH/update hardening, risk posture, exposure review, OpenClaw cron scheduling for periodic checks, or version status checks on a machine running OpenClaw (laptop, workstation, Pi, VPS).</description>\\n    <location>~/AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\healthcheck\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>node-connect</name>\\n    <description>Diagnose OpenClaw node connection and pairing failures for Android, iOS, and macOS companion apps. Use when QR/setup code/manual connect fails, local Wi-Fi works but VPS/tailnet does not, or errors mention pairing required, unauthorized, bootstrap token invalid or expired, gateway.bind, gateway.remote.url, Tailscale, or plugins.entries.device-pair.config.publicUrl.</description>\\n    <location>~/AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\node-connect\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>openai-whisper-api</name>\\n    <description>Transcribe audio via OpenAI Audio Transcriptions API (Whisper).</description>\\n    <location>~/AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\openai-whisper-api\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>skill-creator</name>\\n    <description>Create, edit, improve, or audit AgentSkills. Use when creating a new skill from scratch or when asked to improve, review, audit, tidy up, or clean up an existing skill or SKILL.md file. Also use when editing or restructuring a skill directory (moving files to references/ or scripts/, removing stale content, validating against the AgentSkills spec). Triggers on phrases like &quot;create a skill&quot;, &quot;author a skill&quot;, &quot;tidy up a skill&quot;, &quot;improve this skill&quot;, &quot;review the skill&quot;, &quot;clean up the skill&quot;, &quot;audit the skill&quot;.</description>\\n    <location>~/AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\skill-creator\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>video-frames</name>\\n    <description>Extract frames or short clips from videos using ffmpeg.</description>\\n    <location>~/AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\video-frames\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>weather</name>\\n    <description>Get current weather and forecasts via wttr.in or Open-Meteo. Use when: user asks about weather, temperature, or forecasts for any location. NOT for: historical weather data, severe weather alerts, or detailed meteorological analysis. No API key needed.</description>\\n    <location>~/AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\weather\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>find-skills</name>\\n    <description>Helps users discover and install agent skills when they ask questions like &quot;how do I do X&quot;, &quot;find a skill for X&quot;, &quot;is there a skill that can...&quot;, or express interest in extending capabilities. This skill should be used when the user is looking for functionality that might exist as an installable skill.</description>\\n    <location>~/.agents\\\\skills\\\\find-skills\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>firecrawl</name>\\n    <description>Web scraping, search, crawling, and page interaction via the Firecrawl CLI. Use this skill whenever the user wants to search the web, find articles, research a topic, look something up online, scrape a webpage, grab content from a URL, extract data from a website, crawl documentation, download a site, or interact with pages that need clicks or logins. Also use when they say &quot;fetch this page&quot;, &quot;pull the content from&quot;, &quot;get the page at https://&quot;, or reference scraping external websites. This provides real-time web search with full page content extraction and interact capabilities — beyond what Claude can do natively with built-in tools. Do NOT trigger for local file operations, git commands, deployments, or code editing tasks.</description>\\n    <location>~/.agents\\\\skills\\\\firecrawl\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>firecrawl-agent</name>\\n    <description>AI-powered autonomous data extraction that navigates complex sites and returns structured JSON. Use this skill when the user wants structured data from websites, needs to extract pricing tiers, product listings, directory entries, or any data as JSON with a schema. Triggers on &quot;extract structured data&quot;, &quot;get all the products&quot;, &quot;pull pricing info&quot;, &quot;extract as JSON&quot;, or when the user provides a JSON schema for website data. More powerful than simple scraping for multi-page structured extraction.</description>\\n    <location>~/.agents\\\\skills\\\\firecrawl-agent\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>firecrawl-crawl</name>\\n    <description>Bulk extract content from an entire website or site section. Use this skill when the user wants to crawl a site, extract all pages from a docs section, bulk-scrape multiple pages following links, or says &quot;crawl&quot;, &quot;get all the pages&quot;, &quot;extract everything under /docs&quot;, &quot;bulk extract&quot;, or needs content from many pages on the same site. Handles depth limits, path filtering, and concurrent extraction.</description>\\n    <location>~/.agents\\\\skills\\\\firecrawl-crawl\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>firecrawl-download</name>\\n    <description>Download an entire website as local files — markdown, screenshots, or multiple formats per page. Use this skill when the user wants to save a site locally, download documentation for offline use, bulk-save pages as files, or says &quot;download the site&quot;, &quot;save as local files&quot;, &quot;offline copy&quot;, &quot;download all the docs&quot;, or &quot;save for reference&quot;. Combines site mapping and scraping into organized local directories.</description>\\n    <location>~/.agents\\\\skills\\\\firecrawl-download\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>firecrawl-instruct</name>\\n    <description>Control and interact with a live browser session on any scraped page — click buttons, fill forms, navigate flows, and extract data using natural language prompts or code. Replaces the old firecrawl-browser command. Use when the user needs to interact with a webpage beyond simple scraping: logging into a site, submitting forms, clicking through pagination, handling infinite scroll, navigating multi-step checkout or wizard flows, or when a regular scrape failed because content is behind JavaScript interaction. Also useful for authenticated scraping via profiles. Triggers on &quot;browser&quot;, &quot;instruct&quot;, &quot;click&quot;, &quot;fill out the form&quot;, &quot;log in to&quot;, &quot;sign in&quot;, &quot;submit&quot;, &quot;paginated&quot;, &quot;next page&quot;, &quot;infinite scroll&quot;, &quot;interact with the page&quot;, &quot;navigate to&quot;, &quot;open a session&quot;, or &quot;scrape failed&quot;.</description>\\n    <location>~/.agents\\\\skills\\\\firecrawl-instruct\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>firecrawl-map</name>\\n    <description>Discover and list all URLs on a website, with optional search filtering. Use this skill when the user wants to find a specific page on a large site, list all URLs, see the site structure, find where something is on a domain, or says &quot;map the site&quot;, &quot;find the URL for&quot;, &quot;what pages are on&quot;, or &quot;list all pages&quot;. Essential when the user knows which site but not which exact page.</description>\\n    <location>~/.agents\\\\skills\\\\firecrawl-map\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>firecrawl-scrape</name>\\n    <description>Extract clean markdown from any URL, including JavaScript-rendered SPAs. Use this skill whenever the user provides a URL and wants its content, says &quot;scrape&quot;, &quot;grab&quot;, &quot;fetch&quot;, &quot;pull&quot;, &quot;get the page&quot;, &quot;extract from this URL&quot;, or &quot;read this webpage&quot;. Handles JS-rendered pages, multiple concurrent URLs, and returns LLM-optimized markdown. Use this instead of WebFetch for any webpage content extraction.</description>\\n    <location>~/.agents\\\\skills\\\\firecrawl-scrape\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>firecrawl-search</name>\\n    <description>Web search with full page content extraction. Use this skill whenever the user asks to search the web, find articles, research a topic, look something up, find recent news, discover sources, or says &quot;search for&quot;, &quot;find me&quot;, &quot;look up&quot;, &quot;what are people saying about&quot;, or &quot;find articles about&quot;. Returns real search results with optional full-page markdown — not just snippets. Provides capabilities beyond Claude&apos;s built-in WebSearch.</description>\\n    <location>~/.agents\\\\skills\\\\firecrawl-search\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>remotion-best-practices</name>\\n    <description>Best practices for Remotion - Video creation in React</description>\\n    <location>~/.agents\\\\skills\\\\remotion-best-practices\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>self-improvement</name>\\n    <description>Captures learnings, errors, and corrections to enable continuous improvement. Use when: (1) A command or operation fails unexpectedly, (2) User corrects Claude (&apos;No, that&apos;s wrong...&apos;, &apos;Actually...&apos;), (3) User requests a capability that doesn&apos;t exist, (4) An external API or tool fails, (5) Claude realizes its knowledge is outdated or incorrect, (6) A better approach is discovered for a recurring task. Also review learnings before major tasks.</description>\\n    <location>~/.agents\\\\skills\\\\self-improving-agent\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n</available_skills>\",\n      \"skills\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"clawflow\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"clawflow-inbox-triage\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"coding-agent\",\n          \"requiredEnv\": []\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"gemini\",\n          \"requiredEnv\": []\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"gh-issues\",\n          \"primaryEnv\": \"GH_TOKEN\",\n          \"requiredEnv\": []\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"github\",\n          \"requiredEnv\": []\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"healthcheck\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"node-connect\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"openai-whisper-api\",\n          \"primaryEnv\": \"OPENAI_API_KEY\",\n          \"requiredEnv\": [\n            \"OPENAI_API_KEY\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"skill-creator\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"video-frames\",\n          \"requiredEnv\": []\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"weather\",\n          \"requiredEnv\": []\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"find-skills\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"firecrawl\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"firecrawl-agent\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"firecrawl-crawl\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"firecrawl-download\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"firecrawl-instruct\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"firecrawl-map\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"firecrawl-scrape\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"firecrawl-search\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"remotion-best-practices\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"self-improvement\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"resolvedSkills\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"clawflow\",\n          \"description\": \"Use when work should span one or more detached tasks but still behave like one job with a single owner context. ClawFlow is the runtime substrate under authoring layers like Lobster, acpx, or plain code. Keep conditional logic in the caller; use ClawFlow for flow identity, waiting, outputs, and user-facing emergence.\",\n          \"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\clawflow\\\\SKILL.md\",\n          \"baseDir\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\clawflow\",\n          \"source\": \"openclaw-bundled\",\n          \"sourceInfo\": {\n            \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\clawflow\\\\SKILL.md\",\n            \"source\": \"openclaw-bundled\",\n            \"scope\": \"project\",\n            \"origin\": \"top-level\",\n            \"baseDir\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\clawflow\"\n          },\n          \"disableModelInvocation\": false\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"clawflow-inbox-triage\",\n          \"description\": \"Example ClawFlow authoring pattern for inbox triage. Use when messages need different treatment based on intent, with some routes notifying immediately, some waiting on outside answers, and others rolling into a later summary.\",\n          \"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\clawflow-inbox-triage\\\\SKILL.md\",\n          \"baseDir\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\clawflow-inbox-triage\",\n          \"source\": \"openclaw-bundled\",\n          \"sourceInfo\": {\n            \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\clawflow-inbox-triage\\\\SKILL.md\",\n            \"source\": \"openclaw-bundled\",\n            \"scope\": \"project\",\n            \"origin\": \"top-level\",\n            \"baseDir\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\clawflow-inbox-triage\"\n          },\n          \"disableModelInvocation\": false\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"coding-agent\",\n          \"description\": \"Delegate coding tasks to Codex, Claude Code, or Pi agents via background process. Use when: (1) building/creating new features or apps, (2) reviewing PRs (spawn in temp dir), (3) refactoring large codebases, (4) iterative coding that needs file exploration. NOT for: simple one-liner fixes (just edit), reading code (use read tool), thread-bound ACP harness requests in chat (for example spawn/run Codex or Claude Code in a Discord thread; use sessions_spawn with runtime:\\\"acp\\\"), or any work in ~/clawd workspace (never spawn agents here). Claude Code: use --print --permission-mode bypassPermissions (no PTY). Codex/Pi/OpenCode: pty:true required.\",\n          \"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\coding-agent\\\\SKILL.md\",\n          \"baseDir\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\coding-agent\",\n          \"source\": \"openclaw-bundled\",\n          \"sourceInfo\": {\n            \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\coding-agent\\\\SKILL.md\",\n            \"source\": \"openclaw-bundled\",\n            \"scope\": \"project\",\n            \"origin\": \"top-level\",\n            \"baseDir\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\coding-agent\"\n          },\n          \"disableModelInvocation\": false\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"gemini\",\n          \"description\": \"Gemini CLI for one-shot Q&A, summaries, and generation.\",\n          \"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\gemini\\\\SKILL.md\",\n          \"baseDir\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\gemini\",\n          \"source\": \"openclaw-bundled\",\n          \"sourceInfo\": {\n            \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\gemini\\\\SKILL.md\",\n            \"source\": \"openclaw-bundled\",\n            \"scope\": \"project\",\n            \"origin\": \"top-level\",\n            \"baseDir\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\gemini\"\n          },\n          \"disableModelInvocation\": false\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"gh-issues\",\n          \"description\": \"Fetch GitHub issues, spawn sub-agents to implement fixes and open PRs, then monitor and address PR review comments. Usage: /gh-issues [owner/repo] [--label bug] [--limit 5] [--milestone v1.0] [--assignee @me] [--fork user/repo] [--watch] [--interval 5] [--reviews-only] [--cron] [--dry-run] [--model glm-5] [--notify-channel -1002381931352]\",\n          \"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\gh-issues\\\\SKILL.md\",\n          \"baseDir\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\gh-issues\",\n          \"source\": \"openclaw-bundled\",\n          \"sourceInfo\": {\n            \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\gh-issues\\\\SKILL.