G1vXZvlksGXyysdEwFnR7Su|fc_0d382a4b1258261d0169d2c5689f208191b16d7a122701930e\",\"toolName\":\"read\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\r\\n  \\\"contract_version\\\": \\\"s4.candidate_set.v1\\\",\\r\\n  \\\"target_id\\\": \\\"t001\\\",\\r\\n  \\\"canonical_label\\\": \\\"Hotel Quitandinha\\\",\\r\\n  \\\"target_type\\\": \\\"architectural_anchor\\\",\\r\\n  \\\"scene_ids\\\": [\\r\\n    \\\"scene_003\\\",\\r\\n    \\\"scene_004\\\",\\r\\n    \\\"scene_015\\\",\\r\\n    \\\"scene_046\\\",\\r\\n    \\\"scene_065\\\",\\r\\n    \\\"scene_099\\\",\\r\\n    \\\"scene_123\\\",\\r\\n    \\\"scene_144\\\",\\r\\n    \\\"scene_147\\\"\\r\\n  ],\\r\\n  \\\"candidates\\\": [\\r\\n    {\\r\\n      \\\"candidate_id\\\": \\\"c001\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"source_url\\\": \\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pal%C3%A1cio_Quitandinha\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"page_title\\\": \\\"Palácio Quitandinha - Wikipedia\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"en.wikipedia.org\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"preliminary_classification\\\": \\\"factual_evidence\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"rationale\\\": \\\"The Palácio Quitandinha is a historic former luxury casino hotel in Petrópolis, State of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. In 1947, the Palácio Quitandinha was the site of the Rio Treaty, attended by United States President Harry Truman. Designed by Italian architect Luis Fossatti, and constructed ...\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"confidence\\\": 0.75,\\r\\n      \\\"licensing_note\\\": \\\"public_domain_or_cc\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"acquisition_mode\\\": \\\"reference_only\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"local_asset_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"preview_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"capture_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-04-05T20:25:13.943243+00:00\\\"\\r\\n    },\\r\\n    {\\r\\n      \\\"candidate_id\\\": \\\"c002\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"source_url\\\": \\\"https://www.rioculturalsecrets.com/quitandinha-palace-in-petropolis/\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"page_title\\\": \\\"Exploring the Magnificence of Quitandinha Palace in Petropolis - Rio Cultural Secrets\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"www.rioculturalsecrets.com\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"preliminary_classification\\\": \\\"factual_evidence\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"rationale\\\": \\\"The palace is now home to the Quitandinha Palace Hotel &amp; Convention Center, offering visitors a chance to experience the grandeur of the past. The hotel’s guest rooms provide a taste of the luxurious lifestyle once synonymous with the palace. One of the palace’s most notable attractions is the History and Culture Museum, where visitors can delve into the fascinating past of both the court and the Petropolis region. The museum houses a collection of artifacts, photographs, and documents that tell the story of the palace’s creation and evolution.\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"confidence\\\": 0.7,\\r\\n      \\\"licensing_note\\\": \\\"unknown\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"acquisition_mode\\\": \\\"reference_only\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"local_asset_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"preview_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"capture_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-04-05T20:25:13.943243+00:00\\\"\\r\\n    },\\r\\n    {\\r\\n      \\\"candidate_id\\\": \\\"c003\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"source_url\\\": \\\"https://www.hotels.com/nh11045487/hotels-in-quitandinha-petropolis-brazil/\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"page_title\\\": \\\"Top 10 Hotels in Quitandinha, Petrópolis | Hotels.com\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"www.hotels.com\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"preliminary_classification\\\": \\\"factual_evidence\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"rationale\\\": \\\"Crystal PalaceOpens in a new window – Discover the stunning architecture of this monument, which is a true gem in Quitandinha. As you wander through its elegant structure, take in the intricate details that tell stories of the past. Don’t forget to capture some photos of the breathtaking surroundings that make this spot so iconic! Imperial MuseumOpens in a new window – Step inside this fascinating history museum to explore Brazil&#x27;s rich heritage.\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"confidence\\\": 0.8,\\r\\n      \\\"licensing_note\\\": \\\"unknown\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"acquisition_mode\\\": \\\"reference_only\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"local_asset_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"preview_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"capture_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-04-05T20:25:13.943243+00:00\\\"\\r\\n    },\\r\\n    {\\r\\n      \\\"candidate_id\\\": \\\"c004\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"source_url\\\": \\\"https://www.loc.gov/item/2022687325/\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"page_title\\\": \\\"The Hotel Quitandinha, Petropolis, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil | Library of Congress\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"www.loc.gov\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"preliminary_classification\\\": \\\"factual_evidence\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"rationale\\\": \\\"Ríos Lanz, Ernesto, photographer. The Hotel Quitandinha, Petropolis, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. Petrópolis Brazil Rio De Janeiro, None. [Between 2008 and 2016] Photograph.\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"confidence\\\": 0.8,\\r\\n      \\\"licensing_note\\\": \\\"unknown\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"acquisition_mode\\\": \\\"reference_only\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"local_asset_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"preview_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"capture_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-04-05T20:25:13.943243+00:00\\\"\\r\\n    },\\r\\n    {\\r\\n      \\\"candidate_id\\\": \\\"c005\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"source_url\\\": \\\"https://accidentallywesanderson.com/places/palacio-quitandinha/\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"page_title\\\": \\\"Palacio Quitandinha | Accidentally Wes Anderson\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"accidentallywesanderson.com\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"preliminary_classification\\\": \\\"factual_evidence\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"rationale\\\": \\\"From exploring art museums in Basel, to not lifting a finger at luxurious hotels, and to visiting charming Swiss chalets, our second trip to the Land of Milk and Honey was just as magical as the first. All aboard! We embark from the end of the world aboard the MS Roald Amundsen on a (shivery) trip of a lifetime! See all &gt; ... It is no wonder that Brazil’s Palacio Quitandinha exudes an air of Old Hollywood as the interior of the hotel was built during the golden age of American cinema, and suitably designed by interior and set designer Dorothy Draper.\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"confidence\\\": 0.65,\\r\\n      \\\"licensing_note\\\": \\\"unknown\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"acquisition_mode\\\": \\\"reference_only\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"local_asset_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"preview_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"capture_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-04-05T20:25:13.943243+00:00\\\"\\r\\n    },\\r\\n    {\\r\\n      \\\"candidate_id\\\": \\\"c006\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"source_url\\\": \\\"https://www.reddit.com/r/ArchitecturalRevival/comments/1dw8pc5/former_hotel_quitandinha_palace_brazil_the/\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"page_title\\\": \\\"r/ArchitecturalRevival on Reddit: Former hotel Quitandinha Palace, Brazil. The exterior of the building is in the Norman style and the interior was decorated by prominent interior designer Dorothy Draper in her anti-minimalist style.\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"www.reddit.com\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"preliminary_classification\\\": \\\"stylistic_inspiration\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"rationale\\\": \\\"It&#x27;s incredibly reminiscent of the Shining&#x27;s Overlook Hotel. ... All of these huge palaces seem to be big for the sake of being big, with a dull, empty interior... I don&#x27;t think I&#x27;ve seen a mansion where I was like yup, these rooms make sense. ... That&#x27;s amazing. What is it used for now? ... There are apartments and venues for events and exhibitions in the building. ... Exterior - fine, but German in Brazil which doesn’t have good connotations.\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"confidence\\\": 0.8,\\r\\n      \\\"licensing_note\\\": \\\"unknown\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"acquisition_mode\\\": \\\"reference_only\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"local_asset_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"preview_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"capture_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-04-05T20:25:13.943243+00:00\\\"\\r\\n    },\\r\\n    {\\r\\n      \\\"candidate_id\\\": \\\"c007\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"source_url\\\": \\\"https://insideinside.org/project/palacio-quitandinha/\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"page_title\\\": \\\"Suite, Palácio Quitandinha (1944)*\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"insideinside.org\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"preliminary_classification\\\": \\\"factual_evidence\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"rationale\\\": \\\"Figure 3: Dorothy Draper, Palácio Quitandinha. Source: Jorge Ferreira Jr. Collection, Photographer Unknown, Year Unknown. ( Source | Accessed : April 7, 2014 ) ... Additional Information: Petrópolis, State of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. Designed by Italian architect Luis Fossatti. Built between 1941 and 1946 as a luxury hotel. Hotel rooms are now privately owned condominiums. Publications/Texts in Print- Eerdmans, Emily. 2011. Regency redux: high style interiors, Napoleonic, classical moderne, and Hollywood regency.\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"confidence\\\": 0.65,\\r\\n      \\\"licensing_note\\\": \\\"unknown\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"acquisition_mode\\\": \\\"reference_only\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"local_asset_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"preview_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"capture_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-04-05T20:25:13.943243+00:00\\\"\\r\\n    },\\r\\n    {\\r\\n      \\\"candidate_id\\\": \\\"c008\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"source_url\\\": \\\"https://www.airial.travel/attractions/brazil/quitandinha-petr%C3%B3polis-5_hQ3V-D\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"page_title\\\": \\\"Quitandinha Petrópolis (2025) – Best of TikTok, Instagram & Reddit Travel Guide\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"www.airial.travel\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"preliminary_classification\\\": \\\"factual_evidence\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"rationale\\\": \\\"Late afternoon, during the golden hour, offers beautiful lighting for both interior and exterior shots, especially at the &#x27;Disco&#x27;. ... Quitandinha was originally built as a luxurious casino and hotel in the 1940s, designed by architect Oscar Niemeyer. It was a hub of glamour and entertainment before facing closure. What architectural styles can be seen at Quitandinha?\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"confidence\\\": 0.65,\\r\\n      \\\"licensing_note\\\": \\\"unknown\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"acquisition_mode\\\": \\\"reference_only\\\",\\r\\n      \\\"local_asset_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"preview_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"capture_path\\\": null,\\r\\n      \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-04-05T20:25:13.943243+00:00\\\"\\r\\n    }\\r\\n  ],\\r\\n  \\\"worker_notes\\\": [\\r\\n    \\\"brave 'Hotel Quitandinha historical photos' -> 5 results\\\",\\r\\n    \\\"brave 'Hotel Quitandinha architecture exterior interior' -> 5 results\\\",\\r\\n    \\\"total unique results: 8\\\"\\r\\n  ],\\r\\n  \\\"warnings\\\": []\\r\\n}\"}],\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1775420776699}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"e1b2adda\",\"parentId\":\"25155d6b\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-05T20:26:16.721Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_zyKd2oD24MwxUYe1ifjHvNZ5|fc_0d382a4b1258261d0169d2c5689f2c81918546c360df91ee75\",\"toolName\":\"read\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n  \\\"contract_version\\\": \\\"s4.target_research_brief.v1\\\",\\n  \\\"job_id\\\": \\\"gate_m2_5\\\",\\n  \\\"batch_id\\\": \\\"batch_001\\\",\\n  \\\"target_id\\\": \\\"t001\\\",\\n  \\\"canonical_label\\\": \\\"Hotel Quitandinha\\\",\\n  \\\"target_type\\\": \\\"architectural_anchor\\\",\\n  \\\"scene_ids\\\": [\\n    \\\"scene_003\\\",\\n    \\\"scene_004\\\",\\n    \\\"scene_015\\\",\\n    \\\"scene_046\\\",\\n    \\\"scene_065\\\",\\n    \\\"scene_099\\\",\\n    \\\"scene_123\\\",\\n    \\\"scene_144\\\",\\n    \\\"scene_147\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"research_modes\\\": [\\n    \\\"factual_evidence\\\",\\n    \\\"visual_reference\\\",\\n    \\\"stylistic_inspiration\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"priority\\\": \\\"critic